Data Prep

The goal is to predict whether a persons income was large (defined in 1994 as more than ($50,000)) or small. The predictors include educational level, work hours per week, native country and so on. The data was obtained from census data.

Modeling

Logistic Regression

Log Reg 1

ctrl<-trainControl(method="none", summaryFunction = twoClassSummary, classProbs = TRUE, savePredictions = TRUE)

lrfull<-train(income~., data=train, method="glm", family="binomial", metric="ROC", trControl=ctrl)

pft<-predict.train(lrfull, type="prob")
rft<-roc(train$income, pft[,2])
rft$auc
## Area under the curve: 0.917
pf<-predict.train(lrfull, newdata=valid, type="prob")
rf<-roc(valid$income, pf[,2] )
rf$auc
## Area under the curve: 0.8974

index<-seq(1:nrow(train))

ctrl <- trainControl(method="cv", index=cvindx, summaryFunction = twoClassSummary, classProbs = TRUE)
tunegrid <- expand.grid(
  .mtry = c(5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30),
  .splitrule = "gini",
